# Plan simple boustrophedon coverage of one polygon (with optional holes).
#
# Served by mowgli_coverage's CoverageServer (`plan_coverage`). The planner is
# deliberately minimal — Fields2Cover v3 headland rings + straight serpentine
# swaths, NO turn planning (the robot is a diff-drive that pivots in place;
# turns belong to the navigation stack, not the coverage planner).
#
# The result carries the plan in TWO forms. `segments` is a list of explicit,
# ordered, individually-drivable pieces (concentric headland rings, outermost
# first, then straight swaths in serpentine order) — GUI display and resume
# bookkeeping only; the BT does NOT dispatch these one at a time. Execution
# uses `drivable_subpaths`: hole-free continuous sub-paths (segments already
# joined by forward turn-around connector arcs) that FTCController drives
# end-to-end per sub-path via a pose cursor, bridging any gap between
# consecutive sub-paths with a blade-off Nav2 transit. No heuristic path
# re-segmentation anywhere.

# Goal
geometry_msgs/Polygon outer_boundary
geometry_msgs/Polygon[] obstacles      # interior holes (>= 3 points each)
float64 mow_angle_deg                  # swath heading in the map frame; < 0 = auto (minimise swath count)
---
# Result
uint8 SEGMENT_RING=0    # densified closed headland loop
uint8 SEGMENT_SWATH=1   # straight mainland swath

bool success
string message                         # failure reason when success == false
# GUI / resume bookkeeping ONLY — the BT does not dispatch these one at a
# time; execution (including the resume-cursor staleness fingerprint,
# mowgli_behavior area_plan_fingerprint) is keyed off drivable_subpaths below,
# not this field. Kept for the GUI plan view and PlanCoverageArea's own
# ring/swath-count log line.
nav_msgs/Path[] segments               # ordered drivable segments (rings out→in, then swaths)
uint8[] segment_types                  # parallel to segments (SEGMENT_*)
nav_msgs/Path full_path                # concatenation of all segments (GUI / visualisation only)
nav_msgs/Path[] drivable_subpaths      # WHAT EXECUTION ACTUALLY DRIVES. Hole-free continuous
                                       # sub-paths in drive order, already joined with forward
                                       # turn-around connector arcs. mowgli_nav2_plugins/
                                       # FTCController drives each end-to-end as ONE
                                       # FollowCoveragePath goal via a pose cursor (one PRE_ROTATE
                                       # pivot to the sub-path-start heading, then tracks
                                       # tightly); FollowStrip bridges the gap between
                                       # consecutive sub-paths with a blade-off Nav2 transit that
                                       # routes around obstacles (issue #333). Exactly one entry
                                       # for a hole-free field (== full_path).
float64 total_distance                 # sum of segment lengths (m)
uint32 ring_count
uint32 swath_count
float64 planning_time_s
---
# Feedback
string phase
